                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3rj49f4b/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>purpose of establishing a Jewish college for the education<lb/> of\n                                        ministers, Readers, &amp; teachers. <persName>Sir Moses\n                                                  Montefiore</persName><lb/> presided. I am glad to\n                                                  <del>say</del> see the so long looked for<lb/>\n                                        Institution is now about being brought into existence,<lb/>\n                                        as a beginning 2000 pounds sterling has been already<lb/>\n                                        subscribed, and of course by now has increased. I also<lb/>\n                                        understand a gentleman is going to endow it.<lb/> The case\n                                        of <persName>Alderman Salomons</persName> for his taking his\n                                        seat &amp; voting<lb/> came before a jury but he was not\n                                        satisfied with<lb/> having 12 men that did not understand\n                                        the law deciding<lb/> for him, &amp; he took a verdict\n                                        against himself, subject<lb/> to the opinion of the judges,\n                                        the cause has been argued<lb/> by them but the judges of the\n                                        course of Exchequer have<lb/> not yet give their\n                                                  <sic>judgement</sic>.</p>\n                              <p>I asked <persName>Mr. Henry Mack</persName> to become a subscriber\n                                        to your<lb/>\n                                        <sic>occident</sic> but he refused on account of taking so\n                                        many<lb/> papers in. I think if you had <sic>staid</sic>\n                                        here longer<lb/> and had seen the people themselves you\n                                        might have<lb/> got more subscribers.</p>\n                              <p>As <persName>Mr. Jonas</persName> wrote you last week all the\n                                                  <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName><lb/> News I have\n                                        none to write.</p>\n                              <p>My Aunt &amp; Uncle <persName>Mr. &amp; Mrs. Jonas</persName> send\n                                        their regards<lb/> to you, and accept the same from me\n                                        hoping you<lb/> may succeed in your undertakings which I\n                                        consider are<lb/> for the benefit of the Jewish nation.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">I remain yours truly,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Samuel J Oppenheim</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>To <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3rj49f4b/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
